Germany’s States May Reject Swiss Bank Tax Deal, FTD Reports

-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 
2011-09-12T06:42:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/germany-s-states-may-reject-swiss-bank-tax-deal-ftd-reports.html
Germany ’s upper house of parliament
may reject a draft agreement with  Switzerland  on the taxation of
Swiss bank accounts held by Germans, the  Financial Times
Deutschland  reported, citing comments by opposition officials.  Social Democrats , who can block legislation in the chamber,
are threatening the accord announced by Finance Minister
 Wolfgang Schaeuble  in July, the newspaper  said  today.  Germany’s upper house, the Bundesrat, comprises
representatives of the nation’s 16 state governments.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony Czuczka in Berlin at 
 aczuczka@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at  jhertling@bloomberg. 